      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "given that the clock is used to schedule things, an alternative would be to change this to a steady clock. This will behave better if the system clock is adjusted. However std::chrono::steady_clock is not mockable, which I think is fine in this context here.\r\n\r\n```suggestion\r\n            auto current_time{std::chrono::steady_clock::now()};\r\n```",
