      "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body" : "`steady_clock::now()` returns `steady_clock::time_point` and this results in compilation error in the next line (`last_log_time + SYNC_LOG_INTERVAL < current_time` - `no operator \"<\" matches these operands`).\r\n\r\nWith `duration_cast`, it seems to work.\r\n\r\n```diff\r\n- auto current_time{GetTime<std::chrono::seconds>()};\r\n+ auto current_time{std::chrono::duration_cast<std::chrono::seconds>(std::chrono::steady_clock::now().time_since_epoch())};\r\n```",
      "commit_id" : "626b636b193baae81a697febd41a712f94a8a702",
      "created_at" : "2022-05-07T06:01:21Z",
      "diff_hunk" : "@@ -160,7 +160,7 @@ void BaseIndex::ThreadSync()\n                 pindex = pindex_next;\n             }\n \n-            int64_t current_time = GetTime();\n+            auto current_time{GetTime<std::chrono::seconds>()};",
